        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1962-11-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1962-11-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="113"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d113">
                <head>113. Memorandum for the Record<note n="0" type="source" xml:id="d113fn0"
                        >Source: Washington National Records Center, <gloss target="#t_RG1"
                            >RG</gloss> 330, <gloss target="#t_OSD1">OSD</gloss> Files: <gloss
                            target="#t_FRC1">FRC</gloss> 66 A 3542, 110.01 <gloss target="#t_FY1"
                            >FY</gloss> 64 (23 Nov 62). No classification marking. Drafted by
                            <persName corresp="#p_GRL1">Gilpatric</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Hyannis Port</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1962-11-23">November 23, 1962</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Second Meeting with the President on <gloss target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss> 64
                        DoD Budget Issues<note n="1" xml:id="d113fn1">The meeting was held in the
                                <persName>Kennedy</persName> Compound at Hyannis Port,
                            Massachusetts, where the President was spending the Thanksgiving
                            weekend. The first meeting has not been identified.
                                (<persName>Kennedy</persName> Library, President’s Appointment
                            Book)</note>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <p>At this morning’s meeting with the President (attended by <persName
                        corresp="#p_MNRS1">McNamara</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_TMD1"
                        >Taylor</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_GRL1">Gilpatric</persName>,
                        <persName corresp="#p_HCJ1">Hitch</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_BH8"
                        >Brown</persName>
                    <note n="2" xml:id="d113fn2">
                        <persName corresp="#p_HCJ1">Charles J. Hitch</persName>, Assistant Secretary
                        (Comptroller) of Defense, and <persName corresp="#p_BH8">Harold
                            Brown</persName>, Director of Defense Research and Engineering.</note>
                    for DoD; <persName corresp="#p_BDE1">Bell</persName> and <persName
                        corresp="#p_SEB1">Staats</persName>
                    <note n="3" xml:id="d113fn3">
                        <persName corresp="#p_SEB1">Elmer B. Staats</persName>, Deputy Director of
                        the Bureau of the Budget.</note> for BoB; and <persName corresp="#p_BMG2"
                        >Bundy</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_WJB1">Wiesner</persName> for the
                    White House), the Secretary of Defense’s draft memoranda of November 20 and 21,
                    1962, on the following three subjects<note n="4" xml:id="d113fn4">See <ref
                            target="#d112">Document 112</ref>, <ref target="#d107fn3">footnote 3 to
                            Document 107</ref>, and <ref target="#d111">Document 111</ref>.</note>
                    were considered with the results indicated below, in each instance subject to a
                    general reservation for all concerned pending a final review of the total budget
                    amounts:</p>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="italic">I. Strategic Retaliatory Forces</hi>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Minuteman Program—Approval given to <gloss target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss> 66
                        force level of 950, of which 150 will be improved Minuteman.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Polaris Program— <list>
                            <label>(a)</label>
                            <item>Approval given to 6 additional submarines (completing planned
                                force of 41).</item>
                            <label>(b)</label>
                            <item>A3A missile proposal disapproved.</item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>Skybolt—Cancellation approved subject to consultation with the U.K. on
                        alternatives.</item>
                    <pb facs="0448" n="416" xml:id="pg_416"/>
                    <label>4.</label>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_SAC1">SAC</gloss> Hardened Support Center—Approved in
                        principle, with preference for a location as near as possible to present
                            <gloss target="#t_SAC1">SAC</gloss> Headquarters.</item>
                </list>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="italic">II. B-70</hi>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>RS-70—Approval given to recommendation not to proceed with full
                        development but with addition of $50 million of <gloss target="#t_FY1"
                            >FY</gloss> 63 funds for sensor components.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Reconnaissance Aircraft—R-X concept approved with program decisions to be
                        made following validation of requirements.</item>
                </list>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="italic">III. Nike-Zeus</hi>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Recommendation to defer deployment decision approved.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Approval given to development program recommended by the Secretary of
                        Defense.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GRL1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Roswell Gilpatric</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
